# n8n Workflow Builder

## Overview
This skill helps create production-ready n8n workflows with proper error handling, webhook configuration, and node setup.

## Workflow Structure
n8n workflows are JSON files with this structure:
```json
{
  "name": "Workflow Name",
  "nodes": [],
  "connections": {},
  "settings": {
    "executionOrder": "v1"
  }
}
```

## Common Node Types

### Webhook Trigger
```json
{
  "name": "Webhook",
  "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
  "position": [250, 300],
  "parameters": {
    "httpMethod": "POST",
    "path": "your-webhook-path",
    "responseMode": "onReceived"
  }
}
```

### HTTP Request
```json
{
  "name": "HTTP Request",
  "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
  "position": [450, 300],
  "parameters": {
    "method": "POST",
    "url": "https://api.example.com/endpoint",
    "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
    "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth"
  }
}
```

### Code Node (JavaScript)
```json
{
  "name": "Transform Data",
  "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
  "position": [650, 300],
  "parameters": {
    "jsCode": "return items.map(item => ({ json: { transformed: item.json } }));"
  }
}
```

## Best Practices
1. Always add error handling nodes
2. Use environment variables for credentials
3. Add "No Operation" nodes for branching clarity
4. Test with sample data before production
5. Document workflow purpose in description

## Validation
Run `scripts/validate_workflow.py` to check:
- All required fields present
- Node connections valid
- No orphan nodes
- Credentials referenced correctly
